  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Age.</strong> Kobolds reach maturity within a handful of years, and can live for a couple of centuries, should they not meet an early end defending their homes.<br /><br /><strong>Creature Type.</strong> You are a Humanoid.<br /><br /><strong>Size.</strong> You are Small.<br /><br /><strong>Speed.</strong> Your Speed is 30 feet.<br /><br /><strong>Darkvision.</strong> You have Darkvision to a range of 60 feet.<br /><br /><strong>Draconic Cry.</strong> As a Bonus Action, you let out a cry at your enemies within 10 feet of you. Until the start of your next turn, you and your allies have Advantage on attack rolls against any of those enemies who could hear you. You can use this trait a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.<br /><br /><strong>Fidgety Hands.</strong> Your small hands are quick and nimble, allowing them to get into places they should not or to perform movements of fine motor skills. Your bare hands are considered to be both tinker's tools and thieves' tools, and you are considered proficient in both without requiring either tools.<br /><br /><strong>Kobold Legacy.</strong> Kobolds' connection to dragons can manifest in unpredictable ways in an individual kobold. Choose one of the following legacy options for your kobold:</p><p><strong>Craftiness.</strong> You have proficiency in one of the following skills of your choice: Arcana, Investigation, Medicine, Sleight of Hand, or Survival.</p><p>Additionally, when you make an ability check that you are proficient in, you can roll a d4 and add it to result. You can use this trait a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.</p><p><strong>Defiance.</strong> You have Advantage on ability checks and saving throws to avoid or end the &amp;Reference[Frightened apply=false], &amp;Reference[Grappled apply=false], and &amp;Reference[Restrained apply=false] condition on yourself.</p><p><strong>Draconic Sorcery.</strong> You know one cantrip of your choice from the sorcerer spell list. Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma is your spellcasting ability for that cantrip (choose when you select this species).</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
